[Crim. No. 1609. Third Appellate District. April 4, 1938.] THE PEOPLE, Respondent, v. R. G. PETREWYMER, Appellant.

*590No appearance for Appellant.

U. S. Webb, Attorney-General, and Wilmer W. Morse, Deputy Attorney-General, for Respondent.

THE COURT.

The appellant was convicted in the Superior Court of Stanislaus County of the crime of issuing bank check with intent to defraud, a felony.

The transcript on appeal was filed in this court January 20, 1938. No brief has been filed in behalf of appellant. The cause was regularly placed on the calendar for oral argument on April 4, 1938. No appearance was made for appellant at the time the case was called for hearing.

Pursuant to the provisions of section 1253 of the Penal Code the judgment and the order are affirmed.
